  1→/*! @file csv_encoder.c
  2→ * @brief CSV encoder for streaming analog and digital samples.
  3→ *
  4→ * Encodes sample data into a human-readable CSV format optimized for:
  5→ * - Only outputs enabled channels (reduces file size dramatically)
  6→ * - Self-documenting header with device info and column names
  7→ * - Per-channel timestamps for accurate timing analysis
  8→ * - Calibrated millivolt values for immediate use
  9→ *
 10→ * Uses fast integer-to-string conversion to avoid snprintf overhead
 11→ * in the hot path (data rows). Header generation uses snprintf for
 12→ * simplicity since it runs only once per session.
 13→ */
 14→
